[SN]TITLE[SN]
Two in court over £215,000 of cocaine discovered in Aberdeen

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Two men have appeared in court after cocaine with an estimated street value of more than £215,000 was recovered in Aberdeen.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police Scotland said the drugs were found in a vehicle in the Oscar Road area of Torry on Thursday.
Clarke Davidson, 21, of Stonehaven, and Harry Davidson, 23, of Aberdeen, appeared at Aberdeen Sheriff Court. They made no plea.
Clarke Davidson was released on bail and his co-accused was remanded in custody.
